od. None would be the wiser of the weight he currently carried, save for those close to him perhaps.  Standing over the pond he gazed at the cherry tree, lost in thought. ", "link_list": [], "image_list": [], "html": "It had been a while since Takahashi had stepped foot in the mansion... The hard wood folks , the stone pathways, the man made pond all things that greeted him like a warm welcome from a distant family.  "}, "post-85271": {"user": "Zu Fu", "user_num": 2798, "timestamp": "1537600719000", "message": "The garden and courtyard was a peaceful setting at this time of year and Zu Fu found that he was increasingly happy to go explore the mansion. The gardens were a great place for meditation and the courtyard equally good for pondering and thinking without too much stress to the mind. Zu found the most peculiar little spirits all over the place and with a simple bow he would greet them whenever he came upon one - the same way he greeted the servants and samurai that roamed these streets. Suddenly however Zu Fu stopped as he noticed another soul - this one clad in human hide looking tranquil to at first glance. However the spirits around him seemed to tell another story one of sorrow and grief as he stood there at the pond and looking at one of the large cherry trees. Zu Fu put his hands on his back as he walked up besides Takahashi in his own pace. He took his time glancing over the pond enjoying its stillness in contrast to the ever changing shape of the tree before he addressed Takahashi. \"I see a strong man who laments his choices.\" Zu Fu said informally and first now got to get a look at the white menpo that covered the samurai's face. But Zu Fu was an elderly guy and could thus get away with a lot of things the young people couldn't. \"I am Zu Fu - an old man Lord Hizashi was so kind as to let stay here for a while.\" he said with a grin. \"... and you are?\" Zu Fu asked and mused. \"I seem to remember people talking about the frightening samurai with th